<=nrel_sc_text_translation:...	
(*
->[Hospitalization. The regimen in the acute period and until the 10th day of normal body temperature is bed, and with complications - strict bed. Extension of the regime - with caution: do not make sudden movements, do not lift weights, do not strain during bowel movements.

A sharp restriction of the mechanical and chemical stimuli of the mucous membrane of the gastrointestinal tract, the exclusion of foods and dishes that enhance the processes of fermentation and decay in the intestine. In uncomplicated forms, table No. 4a bt, 5-7 days before discharge, change to No. 15. Reception of a complex of vitamins (ascorbic acid - up to 900 mg / day, vitamins B1 and B2 at 9 mg, PP - 60 mg, P - 300 mg / day).

The course of therapy until the 10th day of normal body temperature, regardless of the severity and speed of clinical recovery of the patient. If within 4-5 days there is no fracture in the state - cancel and appoint another.

Levomycetin (chloramphenicol). adults, 20-30 minutes before meals, 50 mg / kg / day, for 4 doses. After normalization of body temperature - 30 mg / kg / day. In cases of impossibility of oral administration (nausea, vomiting, epigastric pain) parenterally - chloramphenicol succinate 3 g per day or ampicillin: for adults, 1–1.5 g 4–6 r / s or after parenteral 6 g / s. trimethoprim (80 mg in tablets) and sulfamethoxazole (400 mg in tablets) - biseptol, bactrim, septrin, cotrimoxazole. adults inside 2 tablets 2 r / d after meals (in severe forms 3 tab) 3-4 weeks.

Treatment of severe, complicated and combined forms is effective parenterally with a combination of ampicillin (6-8 g / day) and gentamicin (240 mg / day). For detoxification in mild cases, heavy drinking (up to 2.5-3 liters per day), enterosorbents 2 hours after eating (enterodesis - 15 g / day, polyphepan - 75 g / day, coal sorbents - 90 g / day) and inhalation oxygen through nasal catheters for 45-60 minutes 3-4 times a day.](*<-lang_en;;*);;
